{
  "stem": "23278.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Never went to the temple, as we call it there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we had the freedom to choose.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And me, I turned to the Protestant Church and remained.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Christian-- I mean, it was a Reform church.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Calvinist Church, the Church of Geneva, which is-- maybe you don't know, but it is at the basis of modern democracy.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's on the pattern of that church that the United States was conceived by the founding fathers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It is a place where you have no hierarchy, where everybody is equally minister, equally qualified.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You have no bishop.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You have nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everybody is the same.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's a low church without candles, without anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, he didn't, but he approved.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He didn't go to any church.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He went to church when I did get married, but otherwise, no.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But me, I taught Sunday school, and I was extremely involved.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remain involved to this day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a synagogue?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't know very much.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There it was an [INAUDIBLE] extremely close community.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't let anybody in, at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew they were Jewish if it was mentioned, but to me didn't mean anything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first time I-- I became aware of the question is in 1936.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was 13 years old and I was-- my-- my father and my grandmother coming from Basel, my father having been a prisoner in Germany so long during the First World War, and because we were half Swiss, half French and all, I learned German early.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't speak it very well because we spoke French at home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father had the idea of taking me to Germany in 1936.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I went to Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the year of the Olympic Games.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
